other_tests.findings: Appendix is dilated and fluid filled, with mucosal hyperemia, and surrounding fat stranding. There is relative lucency of a portion of the right lower lobe centrally, which may represent congenital lobar emphysema. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel loops, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and distal ureters are all within normal limits. A tiny umbilical hernia containing fat is noted. There is a small amount of free fluid in the pelvis.
